🧠 What “mempalace” actually is

MemPalace is an open-source AI memory system created by Milla Jovovich and developer Ben Sigman.

Core idea:

Store everything → never forget → retrieve intelligently

Instead of summarizing or filtering like most AI memory tools, it:
	•	Stores conversations verbatim (nothing discarded)
	•	Organizes them like a memory palace (wings → rooms → closets → drawers)
	•	Uses vector search (ChromaDB) to retrieve relevant context  ￼

⸻

🧱 Architecture (this is the interesting part)

From the repo + docs:
	•	Wings → projects / people
	•	Rooms → subtopics
	•	Closets → compressed summaries (AAAK language)
	•	Drawers → original raw data (source of truth)  ￼

This is basically:

structured memory graph + lossless storage + fast retrieval layer

